# Robotics in Healthcare: Surgical Robots and Rehabilitation Systems

## Overview

This repository contains a comprehensive study on the application of robotics in healthcare, with a primary focus on **surgical robots** and **rehabilitation systems**. The report explores how robotics, artificial intelligence (AI), sensors, and automation are transforming modern medicine by improving surgical precision, enhancing patient recovery, and supporting healthcare professionals in delivering efficient and high-quality care.

## Topics Covered

- Introduction to Healthcare Robotics
- Overview of Robotic Systems in Medicine
- Surgical Robots
  - Architecture and Components
  - Working Principle
  - Types of Surgical Robots
  - Applications
  - Advantages and Limitations
  - Future Trends
- Rehabilitation Robots
  - Types and Working Mechanism
  - Clinical Applications
  - Benefits and Challenges
- Artificial Intelligence in Healthcare Robotics
- Ethical and Safety Considerations
- Future Scope of Medical Robotics
- References

## Key Features

- Detailed explanation of robot-assisted surgery
- Rehabilitation robotics for stroke and mobility recovery
- AI integration in healthcare robotic systems
- Real-world examples including the Da Vinci Surgical System, EksoNR, and ReWalk
- Discussion of emerging technologies such as telesurgery, nanorobotics, and smart rehabilitation systems
- Academic references from IEEE, Springer, WHO, and leading robotics journals

